Upper Arlington City Schools News Article
                    
                




                        

April 9, 2020 update on COVID-19 precautions and distance learning
    

Dear Upper Arlington families,

We’ve come to the end of our second week of distance teaching and learning, and I just want to say a special thank you to you — our families and our students. You have done an amazing job! 
I also want you to know that we’re going to be flexible, and it’s okay to give yourself space and grace during these times. Make sure that you’re paying attention to the well-being of yourselves and your families. It’s okay to step away from the screens. It’s okay to take a break.  

Here’s our reminders and updates for this week — you may also view a video update by clicking here.

No school reminder
This update is coming to you on Thursday this week because this Friday, April 10 is a no school day — so no distance learning. Please make sure you take advantage of this long weekend!

Athletics and facilities closures
As a reminder, all Upper Arlington Schools playgrounds, athletic fields, tennis courts, basketball courts and running tracks are closed, and there is no trespassing. If you have any concerns regarding these facilities in use, please call the Upper Arlington Police Division non-emergency number - 614-459-2800. 

Special events for the class of 2020
We’re hearing lots of things in the news regarding alternate commencement ceremonies for universities and other high schools.  Some schools are going with virtual commencements, while others are rescheduling for dates in the summer or fall.  

We think it’s extremely likely that our current May 24 date for commencement will be postponed on the orders of state and local health officials, and we are awaiting further guidance from health officials on the months ahead.  One thing we don’t want to do is reschedule our graduation, and then have to postpone it yet again.  We simply don’t know when our state leaders will feel it is safe to have such a large gathering of people.

In addition, student voice is very important to Principal Andrew Theado and his team as they research options, and they will be working with students from our senior class to gather their thoughts on commencement and other special senior class events. Please know that we will be sharing with our seniors and their families any updates as soon as we have them.

Progress reports now available
Progress reports for the third quarter (secondary students) and second trimester (elementary students) are available in PowerSchool. To access your student’s progress report, click on “Report Cards” in the Navigation bar on the left side of the page. If you have an elementary student, you can review the Elementary Progress Reports Family Guide, which explains the Standards “Marking Key” and Effort Scale, by clicking here. If you need assistance accessing your PowerSchool account, please contact [email protected].  

Bright spots
Today, I want to say a special thank you to our entire Classified staff — all of the support personnel who quietly keep our district running well all the time, and this is no different during this time. Our custodians and maintenance workers are coming in on a rotating basis to keep our buildings running, our food service and transportation teams are working together to feed kids through our meal distribution program, and all of our secretaries are still running our buildings on a virtual basis. All of the members of our Classified staff care so much and do so much in service to all of us, and we are in their debt.

I also want to thank all of our staff at Burbank Early Childhood School, our preschool. They are doing a great job of attending to the needs of our youngest learners and families.

I want to say, on behalf of our entire UA Schools staff, we have been overwhelmed by all of the messages of support and gratitude you have been sending to us. It is much appreciated. We are blessed to be working for UA Schools with amazing students and fantastic families.

I hope everyone has a great weekend. And, as always, go Bears! 

Sincerely,

Paul Imhoff, Ed.D.
Superintendent, Upper Arlington Schools


    




	



            
            
        

    

